LAGOS  – The need for Nigerians to be full of gratitude to God was part of the message during this year’s 30th interdenominational nine lessons and Carol service of the Cherubim and Seraphim (C&S) Movement Church, Surulere District Headquarters (Ayo Ni O). Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu, Lagos State governor represented by Hon. Gbenga Oyerinde, Special Adviser to Governor on Special Business District, said there was need for Nigerians to withdraw from depression following the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic but to express thanks to God. “Christmas is significant to every Christian as it is in Christ Jesus lie our hope, success and lives. He who delivered us from evil into His light there is a great need to celebrate Him. God has been so faithful despite the challenges. This period demands sober reflections we know this year has been a special year to every one of us in view of all the challenges,” Sanwo-Olu stated. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Calling for caution to avoid further spread of coronavirus, he said, “We are in the second phase of this pandemic every one of us should adhere to every protocols against the pandemic because we do not want to experience casualties. We do not even think we have the resources having gone through #EndSARS saga. At this stage everyone has to do things the right way in order to avoid emergencies.” Prophet Sunday Korode, General Leader of the church noted in his goodwill speech that “Every year we gather to celebrate our Lord Jesus with harvest of songs as a reminder of His reign and enduring spirit. 365 days down the line we have enjoyed the benefits of God’s faithfulness. Our profound gratitude goes to our maker who had us in mind, kept us in His palms and put us in reckoning to witness another tradition of nine lessons and Christmas carol service. Lagos Archdiocese Ordains Four Priests Incarnation, Decarnation And Re-Incarntion (2) “If the traumatic and difficult events that defined this outgoing year is anything to be considered, songs of praise should break forth from our mouths.” Evang. Akin Ekundayo, Chairman 2020 Carol committee, underlined the place of love in making the world better. “My message is simple, we should love one another. If we love one another the way God commands there will be no problem. Most of the challenges we are facing worldwide wouldn’t have been there if the love of God is shown enough” said Ekundayo. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION